The paper proposes a machine learning framework for integrating multi-omic data with domain knowledge, which is a common problem in the field of machine learning. The paper employs deep representation learning and network constraints to address the "big p, small N" problem. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.DB (Databases).
